29	Barcelona Convention COP22	2021-12-07 00:00:00+00	2021-12-10 00:00:00+00	The 22nd Meeting of the Contracting Parties to the Barcelona Convention and its Protocols is scheduled to take place in December 2021.COP 22 is expected to discuss agenda items including: assessing and controlling marine pollution; ensuring sustainable management of natural marine and coastal resources; protecting the marine environment and coastal zones through preventing and reducing, and as far as possible, eliminating pollution; protecting natural and cultural heritage; strengthening solidarity among Mediterranean coastal States; and contributing to improving quality of life.	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_029.png	transnational	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:50.913866+00	2021-04-28 06:24:50.913866+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
30	Reef Futures Symposium	2021-12-12 00:00:00+00	2021-12-17 00:00:00+00	Reef Futures is the only venue that brings together coral restoration practitioners, researchers, students, and resource managers from around the world to share the latest techniques, technologies, and science to dramatically scale-up the impact and reach of coral reef restoration. Whether you are a local resource manager from a small island looking to learn from seasoned hands, or a topical expert looking to make your work meaningful to a local community, Reef Futures is the place to be. Leave your sadness and despair about the state of coral reefs at the door and come help shape the future you want coral reefs to have!	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_030.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:50.922783+00	2021-04-28 06:24:50.922783+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
31	Launch of the Global Alliance on Circular Economy and Resource Efficiency (GACERE)	2021-02-22 00:00:00+00	2021-02-22 00:00:00+00	Bringing together governments and relevant networks and organisations, the Global Alliance on Circular Economy and Resource Efficiency (GACERE) aims to provide a global impetus for initiatives related to the circular economy transition, resource efficiency and sustainable consumption and production, building on efforts being deployed internationally.	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_031.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:50.934538+00	2021-04-28 06:24:50.934538+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
32	G-STIC Conference First Edition	2021-10-24 00:00:00+00	2021-10-27 00:00:00+00	The World Expo in Dubai will focus on knowledge and technologies that are crucial to achieving the 17 Sustainable Development Goals. It will be an accelerator and testing ground for breakthrough technological solutions that the world needs to shape a post-pandemic world and create a better future for all. Its therefore the perfect opportunity to hold the fifth G-STIC conference, the first one taking place outside of Brussels (Belgium).	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_032.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:50.94265+00	2021-04-28 06:24:50.94265+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
33	G-STIC Conference Second Edition	2022-01-17 00:00:00+00	2022-01-19 00:00:00+00	The World Expo in Dubai will focus on knowledge and technologies that are crucial to achieving the 17 Sustainable Development Goals. It will be an accelerator and testing ground for breakthrough technological solutions that the world needs to shape a post-pandemic world and create a better future for all. Its therefore the perfect opportunity to hold the fifth G-STIC conference, the first one taking place outside of Brussels (Belgium).	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_033.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:51.003955+00	2021-04-28 06:24:51.003955+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
34	OCEANVISIONS 2021 SUMMIT	2021-05-18 00:00:00+00	2021-05-21 00:00:00+00	The Ocean Visions 2021 Summit May 18-21, 2021 Towards a Global Ecosystem for Ocean Solutions will bring together a multi-sector community of researchers, innovators, decision-makers, funders, and more to develop roadmaps for solving great ocean challenges including ocean-based solutions to climate, equitable coastal solutions strategies for resilience and adaptation, marine circular economies, ocean & human health, and how to transform research from academia into sustainable businesses. Online Virtual FormatThe Summit will be held virtually on the campus of the Scripps Institution of Oceanography, USA, between May 18-21, 2021. The summit is linked and co-organized with satellite virtual campuses in Hobart, Australia, Cape Town, South Africa, Mindelo, Cabo Verde, and Kiel, Germany.	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_034.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:51.018394+00	2021-04-28 06:24:51.018394+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
35	Addressing marine litter in the Northwest Pacific Region	2021-03-29 00:00:00+00	2021-03-29 00:00:00+00	The first of the 2021 GPML Webinar Series is hosted by our Northwest Pacific (NOWPAP) Regional Node, on 'Addressing Marine Litter in the Northwest Pacific Region'. The GPML will also present on the release of the proof of concept for the GPML Digital Platform Data Hub and next steps for Phase II.	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_035.png	\N	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:51.028609+00	2021-04-28 06:24:51.028609+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
36	Action for the Oceans  Youth leaders raising awareness for the Oceans, together!	2021-11-06 00:00:00+00	2021-11-06 00:00:00+00	Join us for this special hybrid event with a virtual platform to showcase inspiring actions for the oceans from youth leaders around the world!  Peace Boats Ocean and Climate Youth Ambassadors from Small Island Developing States and Youth for the SDGs scholars will be presenting their work from various countries including Fiji, Seychelles, Trinidad and Tobago, India, Mauritius, Chile, Mexico and more. Through a storytelling training program in partnership with the creative changency, Pendulum, this years ocean youth leaders will share their experiences to highlight the 2021 UN World Oceans Day theme of The Ocean: Life and Livelihoods.Through education and outreach, Action for the Oceans aims to strengthen creative skills and innovative solutions to achieve the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals, with a focus on SDG 14 for Life Below Water.Works will be shared via our digital platform and a reception will be held at the Selina Hotel in Chelsea, New York on the evening of June 11, Friday.	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_036.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:51.038858+00	2021-04-28 06:24:51.038858+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
37	COVE Demo Day  Virtual	2021-10-06 00:00:00+00	2021-10-06 00:00:00+00	COVE  Where the best ideas in ocean technology come to life!Located in what was once the Canadian Coast Guard facility on Halifax Harbour, COVE is home to local and global ocean technology businesses, post-secondary institutions, and marine-based and service businesses that support the ocean sector. The COVE site features extensive marine facilities with two large, deep-water piers, office space, an incubator and space for shops and labs.COVE is a community that brings together the best and the brightest to push ocean tech advances to market. Its a space that fosters innovation and cross-pollinates expertise, ideas, and resources among members, COVE is where business growth, opportunity, and technical advances happen.On June 8 and June 10, 2021, attendees of the H2O Conference will have the opportunity to watch the latest in ocean technology highlighted on the Halifax Harbour. One registration to the H2O Conference also gets you access to COVE Demo Day broadcasts, too!	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/events_037.png	global	\N	2021-04-28 06:24:51.045299+00	2021-04-28 06:24:51.045299+00	\N	\N	\N	\N	APPROVED	\N
