48	The Blue Barriers: Collecting plastic waste in rivers before it reaches the sea	\N	826	Startup	Pilot	t	\N	national	[]	Description: Since the beginning of the development of our technology, we have been in search of a simple solution.  To offer a permanent solution that can be scalable in so many different conditions, including where resources are limited simplicity represents high value. That is why we worked to keep the Blue Barriers simple to build, to be installed and to maintain. The structure is made by two parts: floating modules (made of recycled and recyclable polyethylene) and a supporting internal steel structure that makes the barriers rigid and able to resist to challenging river conditions thanks to three steel cable that cross the barriers. We consider several anchorage and mooring system options to adapt at the specific river; however, in case of rivers of a width below 50m we consider an anchorage above the river level, via steel cables. This allows avoiding creating any obstacle in the river flow. In wider rivers, we will choose anchorage in the river bad (deadweights or piles). Images that describes the Blue Barriers structure will be emailed to the address below. The area where the material will be collected will be along the riverbank in order to facilitate the removal of the material also in case of balky debris like logs. The collection area will be equipped by a steel grid that will screen the material, keep an active water flow that will drive the material toward the collection point and when specifically sized will allow the passage of biological components like fish eggs and other water organisms that might float.The system will be equipped with an automatic and manual opening system that will allow disengaging the barriers in case of emergency. The manual system provides a backup of the automatic one and the option of opening the barriers in case of forecasted exceptional floodings.The structure does not require energy to function ones installed. The only energy required will be for the collection of the debris with a mechanical arm with a crab or conveyor belt.The Blue Barriers have been developed with a modular design to fit any size of river, canal or water stream and for minimizing the cost of production, transportation and maintenance.Scientific studies report that a relevant portion of the plastic transported by the rivers accumulated below the water level in the first 50cm of the water column. That is why we designed the barriers in order to sink from 70 to 90 cm.Possible challenges will be the case of the transportation of abundant balky debris (logs, branches etc.). The Barriers structure will be sized to resist to such balky debris and the disengagement systems will be activated in case of exceptional quantities of wood transported.The simplicity of the structure, also, allows us to produce locally the barriers in the country where they will be installed, creating jobs locally and minimizing the environmental footprint of transportation.Plastic recovery capacity: The quantity of plastic collected will depend on the rivers where we will install our solution. Considering the estimate of plastic transported by the 20 most polluted rivers in the world (Lebreton et al, 2017), if we would install our barriers we would collect 1.19Mton of plastic per year.	2021-04-28 06:24:46.654366+00	2021-06-10 08:52:33.83055+00	\N	\N	APPROVED	https://seadefencesolutions.com	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/technology_048.jpg	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/technology_48_logo.png	\N
