39	Plasticoin: Virtual currency in exchange for plastic waste	2020	858	Startup	Pilot	f	info@plasticoin.com.uy	national	[]	Plasticoin is a project in Uruguay that uses virtual currency to incentivize consumers to recycle plastic waste. The currency can be used at restaurants and stores.Nearly 13 million tonnes of plastic waste is not recycled and ends up in the worlds oceans, according to the United Nations. In Uruguay, a country of 3.4 million people, only 35% of plastic waste is collected for recycling.Plasticoin aims to incentivize consumers to deposit their plastic waste in return for virtual currency. The project is undergoing pilot tests at a seaside resort in Piriapolis city on the countrys Atlantic Ocean coast:Consumers can register online and deposit plastic waste from their household or collected from the beach at one of the three designated collection centers. They receive Plasticoin currency on their phone based on the weight and type of waste discarded. The minimum waste is one kg, for which they receive Plasticoins. To promote clean coastal zones, plastic waste and microplastic removed from beaches and oceans results in a higher Plasticoin payment.The customers can use the currency to get discounts at partnered shops and restaurants. These include yoga centers, surfboard shops, and shops selling bags, toothbrushes, pizza, haircuts, and coffee, among other products.Plasticoins launched in January 2020 with a grant of $5000 from the Uruguan governments National Development Agency. The project received more than a thousand users within three weeks, against a target of 100 users in a month.The project is looking for companies that can provide discounts on their products to Plasticoin users. It is also looking for companies to advertise on the Plasticoin platform. Based on the number of Plasticoins received by the company, it can claim tax benefits under a 2019 law passed in the country.	2021-04-28 06:24:46.491745+00	2021-06-10 08:52:34.750667+00	\N	\N	APPROVED	https://www.plasticoin.com.uy/	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/technology_039.jpeg	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/technology_39_logo.png	\N
35	Pinovo: Patented technology for dust-free vacuum blasting of industrial surfaces	2009	578	Established Company	In market	f	info@pinovo.com	national	[]	Pinovo offers an innovative vacuum blasting technology to reduce the amount of microplastics that end up in Norwegian oceans when old paint is removed from industrial surfaces. Pinovos technology and surface maintenance tools drastically reduce waste and emissions and protect the marine ecosystem and human food chain.   While paints are essential for protecting offshore steel structures from corrosion, due to the salt content in oceans, the removal of old paint from the steel surfaces leads to ocean pollution. Currently, the 12-billion-dollar sandblasting industry produces heavy metals, toxic dust, and microplastics too.Pinovo has developed an ATEX-certified closed loop grip basting technology, which is also known as vacuum blasting or dust-free blasting. This technology helps customers save money, improve HSE, and also protect the environment without any compromise being made on the quality of the work. Some of its products are:PiBlast: An automated, fully pneumatic, closed-loop vacuum blasting tool intended for dust-free abrasive blasting of straight pipes.PiCo Pipe: A hand-held closed-loop vacuum blasting tool intended for dust-free abrasive blasting of pipes.PiHab: A flexible, transparent, abrasive blasting enclosure to be used with the Pinovo vacuum blasting units PiSys.PiWalk: A walk-behind tool primarily intended for dust-free vacuum blasting of medium-sized flat or walkable inclined surfaces.PiConnect: A versatile, hand-held closed-loop vacuum blasting tool primarily intended for spot and sweep blasting. Due to the click-on adapter technology, a variety of surface geometries can be blast cleaned easily.PiPoint: A hand-held closed-loop vacuum blasting tool primarily intended for small spots with difficult access.PiSys: A fully pneumatic ATEX certified closed-loop vacuum blasting and recycling unit, designed for dust-free abrasive blastingAll Pinovo products are safe to use, and make activities like blasting, sheeting, cleaning, and painting efficient. Other work disciplines or surrounding equipment are not affected by them. Some other advantages are their low noise emissions, less dust and grit production, low vibration, ergonomic design, light weight, and a robust waste management system.    Pinovo supports the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals, to prevent and significantly reduce marine pollution by 2025, and achieve the environmentally sound management of chemicals and all wastes by 2020.Some companies that Pinovo works with are Shell, Equinor, EDF, AkerBP, Chevron, Repsol Sinopec, and the Norwegian Armed Forces.Their technology is an ideal solution for companies looking for offshore industrial painting and cleaning services. Pinovos distributors are located in France, Benelux, USA, Canada, and Trinidad.	2021-04-28 06:24:46.421406+00	2021-06-10 08:52:34.870039+00	\N	\N	APPROVED	https://www.pinovo.com/	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/technology_035.jpg	https://storage.googleapis.com/akvo-unep-gpml/images/technology_35_logo.png	\N
